Not seen any mention of this, it's been plastered across the UK news for some time and I was wondering what people made of it. Gordon Brown clearly thinks he's saved the world (again), even Bob Geldoff seemed pretty happy about the deal, and Obama was waxing lyrical as he does so well. My economic knowledge isn't really up to critiquing the substance but, were I a betting man, I reckon this drop in the ocean isn't going to do much good.
